Model significance

Is the overall regression significant at 5% level? Justify your answer.

Since this value is approximately 0 and less than 0.05, we can reject the null hypothesis. There is evidence that suggests there is a linear relationship between level of prostate specific antigen and the set of predictor variables.

Coefficient interpretation

Interpret the coefficient of svi.

(2 points)

The coefficient of the svi variable is 0.7662. This means that for a one unit increase in seminal vesicle invasion, the level of prostate specific antigen will increase by 0.7662 units, while holding all other predictor variables constant.

Variable significance

Report the \(p\)-values for gleason and age. What do you conclude about the significance of these variables?

(2+2 points)

The p-value for gleason is 0.775 and the p-value for age is 0.082. Both these values are greater than 0.05, which means there is not enough evidence to reject the null hypothesis that these corresponding coefficients are zero, and suggests that these variables do not have a statisically significant effect on the lpsa variable. It also means that there is no relationship or a weak relationship between the gleason/age and the lpsa and that this relationship is likely to be due to chance.

Model visualisation

Use the model developed in the previous question to plot the regression lines for Africa, Asia, and Europe. Put gdpPerCapita on the vertical axis and \(P\) on the horizontal axis. Use a legend to distinguish among the regression lines of the three continents.

(4 points)

Code 
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (9,6)
sns.set(font_scale = 1.3)
x = np.linspace(soc_ind.gdpPerCapita.min(),soc_ind.gdpPerCapita.max(),100)
ax = sns.lineplot(x = x, y = model.params['lifeFemale']*x+model.params['Intercept'], label='Africa', color = 'red')
plt.plot(x, (model.params['lifeFemale']+model.params['lifeFemale:continent[T.Asia]'])*x+model.params['Intercept']+model.params['continent[T.Asia]'], '-b', label='Asia')
plt.plot(x, (model.params['lifeFemale']+model.params['lifeFemale:continent[T.Europe]'])*x+model.params['Intercept']+model.params['continent[T.Europe]'], '-g', label='Europe')
plt.legend(loc='upper left')
plt.xlabel('Female Life Expectancy')
plt.ylabel('Predicted GDP Per Capita')
plt.show()
